{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport","doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/RelayTransport","doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/CustomTransports"],"anchor":"Topics"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/CustomTransports","doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackTransport","doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport","doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/RelayTransport"],"title":"Transports","generated":true,"anchor":"Transports"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" requires a "},{"code":"token","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter to POST to GitHub Issues. Wherever that token lives — embedded constant, obfuscated blob, fetched at runtime — the threat model is the same: "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"anyone with the binary can recover the token"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":". Disassembly, runtime memory dump, or a hooked HTTPS proxy will eventually surface it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The SDK does not pretend otherwise. It exposes ","type":"text"},{"code":"token: String","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directly and lets you decide the trade-off:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Approach"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Effort","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Resists casual extraction","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Resists determined extraction","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Plaintext constant","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"trivial","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"no","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"XOR \/ obfuscated blob decoded at runtime","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"small","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"yes"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Token fetched from your server at app start","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"medium"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"yes"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"no (once fetched, lives in memory)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Server-side relay holds the token","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"medium-high"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"yes","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"yes"}],"type":"strong"}]}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Only the last row genuinely contains the blast radius. The first three raise the bar; an attacker who actually wants the token will still get it.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Acceptable use of an embedded token","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Acceptable-use-of-an-embedded-token"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A PAT inside the binary is reasonable when:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The repo is a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"write-only"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" feedback inbox and the worst-case abuse is spam issues you can delete."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can rotate the PAT quickly if abuse occurs (and have monitoring to notice).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The PAT’s scope is the minimum that lets it open issues — typically ","type":"text"},{"code":"public_repo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"repo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for a private repo, nothing more.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’re comfortable with someone using the same endpoint to spam your inbox."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If any of these stop being true, move to a relay.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Moving to a relay","level":2,"anchor":"Moving-to-a-relay"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The cleanest mitigation is to keep the credential on a server you control and expose a thin HTTPS endpoint. The SDK ships a ready-made ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/RelayTransport","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for exactly this — point it at your relay’s URL and your app never sees a GitHub token:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let transport = RelayTransport(","    endpoint: URL(string: \"https:\/\/your-relay.example.com\/api\/feedback\")!,","    captchaToken: token   \/\/ optional bot-mitigation token, omitted when nil",")","let feedback = FeedbackClient(appName: \"AcmeApp\", transport: transport)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/RelayTransport","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is wire-compatible with the same relays the AppFeedback Web and Android SDKs target. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/CustomTransports","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" if you need to write your own transport for a different backend.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once the relay holds the token, you also get:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rate-limiting per device \/ IP without burning GitHub’s API quota.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Spam filters before they reach your repo.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional attachments (screenshots, logs) via your own CDN — the GitHub REST API doesn’t accept binary uploads, but your server can mirror to one."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Schema evolution without shipping a new app version."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Dont-store-tokens-in-your-repo","text":"Don’t store tokens in your repo","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even if you’re embedding a PAT in the binary, the source should never have it in plaintext. Common pattern:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep the obfuscated\/encoded form in source."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Decode it at runtime just before constructing the transport.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restrict the PAT scope to issues-write only."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Have a documented rotation procedure."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Secrets and Tokens","roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"AppFeedbackCore"}]},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/SecretsAndTokens"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Shipping a GitHub Personal Access Token inside an app binary is a known trade-off. Here’s how the SDK handles it honestly.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/secretsandtokens"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore/GitHubDirectTransport":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GitHubDirectTransport","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackTransport","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that posts reports directly to the GitHub Issues"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"REST API."}],"url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/githubdirecttransport","title":"GitHubDirectTransport","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GitHubDirectTransport"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore/FeedbackTransport":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"FeedbackTransport"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackTransport","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FeedbackTransport","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/feedbacktransport","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Where a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackReport","type":"reference"},{"text":" gets delivered.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"FeedbackTransport"},"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore/FeedbackReport":{"url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/feedbackreport","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FeedbackReport","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A single user-supplied feedback submission."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FeedbackReport","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"FeedbackReport","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackReport","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore/RelayTransport":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/RelayTransport","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackTransport","type":"reference"},{"text":" that posts reports to an ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"adopter-operated relay"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead of to GitHub directly."}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RelayTransport"}],"url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/relaytransport","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"RelayTransport"}],"role":"symbol","title":"RelayTransport","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore":{"kind":"symbol","title":"AppFeedbackCore","role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"Submit feedback from any Apple platform to a GitHub repository in the exact body format the AppFeedback inbox parses.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore"},"doc://AppFeedbackCore/documentation/AppFeedbackCore/CustomTransports":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport"},{"type":"text","text":" with a relay server, a mock, or any other backend by conforming to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackTransport"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/appfeedbackcore\/customtransports","title":"Custom Transports","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/CustomTransports"}}}